cat
#
# Default interpreter for terminal functions (single underscore prefix: _).
#
# Terminal functions output shell commands. The default interpreter 'cat' displays
# commands without executing them (safe by default).
#
# Security rationale:
# - New users see what commands would run before executing
# - Prevents accidental execution of untrusted operations
# - Principle of least privilege
#
# To enable auto-execution (for experienced users):
#   echo "sh" > .env/local/VPN_SWITCH_TERMINAL_INTERPRETER
#
# Common alternatives:
# - sh: Execute commands directly (opt-in for power users)
# - tee log.txt | sh: Log commands and execute
# - sh -x: Execute with shell tracing
#
# Phase 3.1.2: Intrinsic classification via naming convention (_ prefix).
